    "text": "U.S. Envoy Steve Witkoff reacted furiously to Iran’s 10-point proposal, calling it: “A disaster, a catastrophe.” What followed was described as a: “Chaotic” day of amendments. Pakistan shuttled drafts between the U.S. and Iran, while Egypt and Türkiye tried to bridge gaps. China also quietly urged Iran to find an off-ramp. By Monday night, U.S. approval was secured for a revised two-week ceasefire proposal. Source: Axios",
